{
  "image": "6709\\6709.jpg",
  "title": "Mathew's Big Broadway Bash",
  "description": "Fresh off a hit run at the Toronto Fringe, Mathew's Big Broadway Bash brings powerhouse vocals, heartfelt storytelling, and surprise sing-a-longs. Big voice, bare feet, and all heart. \"A unique Fringe treat.\"- Ross Steve, Front Mezz Junkies",
  "credits": "<strong>Playwright</strong>: Mathew Mac Lean<br/><strong>Director</strong>: Mathew Mac Lean<br/><strong>Cast</strong>: Mathew Mac Lean<br/><strong>Designers</strong>: Mathew Mac Lean<br/><strong>Stage Manager</strong>: Mathew Mac Lean<br/>",
  "website": "https://torontocabaretproductions.com",
  "plain_language": "Mathew’s Big Broadway Bash is a fun and feel-good cabaret show filled with songs from your favourite musicals. It’s not a big Broadway show with big money — it’s a small, heartwarming show made with love, creativity, and a lot of passion. You’ll hear songs from shows like Grease, Cats, Mamma Mia!, The Little Mermaid, Pippin, and The Sound of Music. This is more than just a show — it’s a celebration! We sing, we laugh, and we welcome the audience to join the fun. Whether you sing along quietly or imagine yourself on stage, this night is for you. This cabaret is about community, joy, and making musical theatre more accessible for everyone. It’s bold, a little scrappy (this is Fringe!), and full of heart.",
